<SLUG> BC-THQ-CHICKENVIDEO-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THQ PLUCKS NEW TITLE FOR NINTENTO TOY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT MONROE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CALABASAS, Calif. _ Calabasas-based video game-maker THQ will
make summer blockbuster ``Chicken Run'' into a title for Nintendo's
Game Boy Color handheld toy. The company said the theme of the
movie was a natural match to the Game Boy market, made up of
impulse buyers and parents of young children.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think `Chicken Run' was a coup certainly for the
handheld,'' said Germaine Gioia, vice president of licensing. ``It
jumps off the shelf. Big movies help Game Boy sales.''
</P>
<P>
   Analysts also see the new title as a natural for THQ, which also
makes games such as Wrestlemania 2000. It just adds to an already
positive investment outlook, said Stewart Halpern, an analyst with
Banc of America Securities.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is just another example of what has made THQ the
worldwide leader of third-party publisher of Game Boy games,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   In the game, the player is the Claymation film's protagonist
Ginger and will, of course, lead cooped-up poultry to freedom.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very true to the movie,'' said the game's producer Petro
Piaseckyj. ``You have three to nine chickens following you and
they're very, very stupid.''
</P>
<P>
   The game is scheduled for release in October.
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
