<HEADLINE>
KANSAS' AXTELL SET FOR AUSTRIAN TOUR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Luke Axtell is looking forward to being a part of the upcoming
Big 12 basketball all-stars' tour of Austria.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've heard Austria is really fabulous,'' said the Kansas
senior, one of 12 conference players who are scheduled today to
begin three days of preparation before embarking on the playing
jaunt, Tuesday to Aug. 18.
</P>
<P>
   But Axtell might be just as eager were the tour taking place on
elementary school asphalt courts with chains for nets. Thetour
marks the former Texas player's return to the competitive court
after a self-imposed five-month hiatus. Citing an undisclosed
medical condition, Axtell took a leave of absence from the
Jayhawks' active roster 20 games into last season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm feeling fine, really positive,'' he said. ``I can't wait
to get back to Kansas. I have a lot to prove to myself, a lot to
prove in general. I'm determined to make it through the season and
do the best I can, but I'm feeling really positive about it all
because I have such a head start compared to what I've had other
years.''
</P>
<P>
   Axtell as yet does not want to be specific about why he left the
team.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not saying anything about \Rthe reason\S yet,'' he said.
``Though I am thinking about \Rdoing so\S when it's not a
distraction _ sometime after the season _ because there are some
really loyal \R Kansas\S fans who have stood by me all through this
and they deserve to know something. I just don't feel up to talking
about it yet.
</P>
<P>
   ``I will say this, it was not a sexually transmitted disease,
drug rehabilitation or problems with alcohol.''
</P>
<P>
   Axtell said he looks to the future with new resolve. In addition
to cutting an original 10-song CD this summer in Austin, which is
slated to be released shortly after his return from the Big 12
tour, Axtell has added a new word to his vocabulary _ discipline.
</P>
<P>
   He said he has devoted himself to a strict off-season regimen
the past few months, something he has never done before.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've been getting up at 5:30 in the morning and running with
my granddad. For me, that's pretty impressive. I'm going to come in
this year and be as focused as I can be,'' Axtell said.
</P>
<P>
   Axtell also has worked with a shooting coach, trying to
rediscover the touch that deserted him last season. He has also
been lifting weights.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm in the best shape I've ever been,'' Axtell said.
</P>
<P>
   Joining Axtell in the Big 12 squad are Terry Black (Baylor),
D.J. Harrison (Colorado), Jamaal Tinsley (Iowa State), Quentin
Buchanan (Kansas State), Brian Grawer (Missouri), Cary Cochran
(Nebraska), Nolan Johnson (Oklahoma), Andre Williams (Oklahoma
State), Chris Owens (Texas), Bernard King (Texas A&AMP;M) and Cliff
Owens (Texas Tech).
</P>
<P>
   Ricardo Patton of Colorado will coach the team. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
