<DOCNO> NYT20000805.0054 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-05 10:27 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4418 &Cx1f; var-z
u i BC-MIDEAST-ARABS-REVIEW-     08-05 1052
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MIDEAST-ARABS-REVIEW-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EVERYONE ASKS FOR ARAB UNITY. GETTING IT IS HARDER. 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 By SUSAN SACHS   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAIRO, Egypt _ Political slogans tend to long outlive their
