<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Aug. 6, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   JCC-AFTERMATH (Granada Hills, Calif.) _ In the 12 months since a
gunman shot and injured five people at the North Valley Jewish
Community Center, the center has been striving for normalcy. The
only physical evidence of change are security guards who stand
sentinel at the padlocked iron gates. Otherwise, it's a normal day
at camp; no one talks about the accused gunman or his motives. By
Dana Bartholomew. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   FOSTERKIDS-TURNOUT (Los Angeles) _ At any given time, an
estimated 500 to 1,000 youths are homeless in Los Angeles County
after turning 18 and leaving foster care, due mostly to a lack of
affordable housing, officials say. Critics and the teen-agers
themselves disagree, blaming the county's ``poor history helping
children who leave long-term foster care.'' By Troy Anderson. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
