<P>
   RUSSIA-DACHAS _ MOSCOW _ Summertime in Russia is synonymous with
one thing: dachas, the countryside homes where Russians get away
from everyday life, relax and spend quality time with family and
friends. Dacha culture has existed since Czarist times, and it has
spawned a rich cultural tradition. In Soviet times, these plots
helped people survive amid shortages of food, and the land remained
the only private property allowed. My Russian friends Slava and
Lucy, like millions oapped uncle.
