<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Using Inbox helps make life easier
 &HT;    By Dann Stupp
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ You can find offers for free e-mail accounts,
Web-hosting space and even Internet access throughout the Internet.
But Excite Inbox (www.excite.com/Info/inbox/welcome.html) is
finally offering something of worth _ convenience.
</P>
<P>
   If you're tired of checking multiple e-mail accounts, you can
configure Inbox to check all of your POP3 e-mail addresses from one
place. Your work, school and personal e-mails can be sent to one
mailbox, eliminating the need to log into numerous accounts.
</P>
<P>
   You can also receive faxes and voice mails (with the help of
Real Player or Windows Media Player) from Inbox. You'll be issued a
hefty 10-digit extension to use with the system's main number (888)
392-4832 (3-EXCITE2), but it's a whole lot cheaper than paying for
a voice-mail service, which can run $10 to $15 per month. Faxes can
be viewed like e-mail, and you can listen to voice mails with a
simple mouse click.
</P>
<P>
   This one-stop communications center works great for the business
person on the go or for any small, Web-based business. And with the
backing of Internet powerhouse Excite, the features are likely to
get even sweeter.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
