<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Beat the heat in the dog days of summer
 &HT;    By Alma E. Hill
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Dogged out from the heat? Get yourself into shape with
a little sun sense by protecting your hair and skin from damaging
ultraviolet rays.
</P>
<P>
   You don't have to stay inside if you have the right essentials
to shield you.
</P>
<P>
   Now is the time to double up on sunscreen by using a moisturizer
and a foundation that offer SPF protection.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Hudson, senior makeup artist with the M.A.C. pro team,
says people with normal skin should look for moisturizers and
foundations that have an SPF 15 protection.
</P>
<P>
   ``We all know 15 over 15 doesn't give you 30, but it still gives
you more protection than the SPF 15 sunblock protection would
alone,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Water-based facial spritzes and mists are also good in the
summer heat because they provide instant refreshment without
disturbing makeup.
</P>
<P>
   ``You could use it every 15 minutes and it's not going to hurt
you,'' Hudson says. ``Once you get used to it, you'll get hooked.''
</P>
<P>
   Perfect your tan with bronzing and self-tanning lotions that
provide the color you need without streaking. The proper
application could mean the difference between looking like a
lobster or having a healthy glow.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a definite art to it,'' advises Hudson. ``You've got
to exfoliate first and get any dead skin out of the way. Then it
has to be applied very smoothly and evenly.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
