<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0805: COLOMBIA GRIPPED IN FEAR _ Bands of heavily
armed guerrillas and right-wing paramilitary groups roam the
countryside, warring against each other over ideology and control
of the illegal drug trade. Rural peasants, caught in the middle,
have fled by the thousands, their homes destroyed, businesses
ruined, their children lured or taken at gunpoint to join the
groups of fighters. Colombia is a nation living in fear and
uncertainty. Few are untouched by the country's troubles.
(Williams, Cox Washington Bureau). Art includes a 5-column color
photo of a refugee who has relocated from the rural countryside
into the city.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: WAVE OF KIDNAPPINGS _ Colombia leads the world in
kidnappings, with nearly 3,000 people kidnapped last year. The
result is an epidemic of fear and distrust. (Williams, Cox
Washington Bureau) Art includes a 2-column color photo of a woman
holding a photograph of her kidnapped uncle.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: FINANCIAL AID _ Colombian officials are hoping U.S. and
European aid will help curb the production and distribution of
illegal drugs. (Williams, Cox Washington Bureau) Art includes a
2-column color photo of an army base with newly formed
anti-narcotics battalions.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: WEB SITE _ A box showing where to go on the Web to find
more information about Colombia. Art includes a 6-pica color
illustration of a computer.
</P>
<P>
   END COXNET PAGE
