</P>
<P>
   CITY-CAMPFIRE-KIDS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Today's Camp Fire Boys and
Girls (boys were added in 1975) are more likely to gather in a
housing project than at a campground, and more likely to learn the
skills of surviving in the urban jungle than in the great outdoors.
(Dayton Daily News). 32. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GADGETS-COLUMN _ You can find offers for free e-mail accounts,
Web-hosting space and even Internet access throughout the Internet.
But Excite Inbox (http://www.excite.com/Info/inbox/welcome.html) is
finally offering something of worth _convenience. (Cummings, Dayton
Daily News).
</P>
