<P>
   SANFRAN-NEWSIDE _ SAN FRANCISCO _ Visiting the South of Market
area, the city's new cultural crossroads, a thriving blend of
museums, restaurants, clubs and dot-com businesses. SOMA has
extended downtown's cosmopolitan appeal through a once-seedy
warehouse district south, in the direction of Pacific Bell Park,
the new waterfront home of baseball's Giants. (Sabulis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   SANFRAN-TOUR _ SAN FRANCISCO _ A guide to the best offerings in
the South of Market area. (Sabulis, Atlanta Journal-Constitution.)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ARCTIC-FLIGHT _ Even in summer, you just don't swim in the
Arctic Ocean. It's always cold, so you approach it delicately,
respectfully, with one eye on the ice floes dotting the horizon.
Mid-morning on July 3, pilots Bud Barton, John Keys and Walt Pierce
carefully picked their way over the rocks and pebbles on the shore
by Tuktoyaktuk, Northwest Territories, untied a shoe, stripped off
a sock and dipped a big toe in the shallows. (Grand Junction Daily
Sentinel) 55. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   CHEAP-TRAVEL _ I've received several e-mails recently about bed
and breakfasts and whether they hold any advantages over hotels and
motels. The quick, easy answer is: It depends on your taste, and to
some degree, your budget. (Marcano, Dayton Daily News). 22. MOVED.
