   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NASCAR-INDY _ INDIANAPOLIS _ NASCAR makes its now annual
visit to Indianapolis for the Brickyard 400, a Saturday afternoon
race. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 13.
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALLBBO-100MPH-PITCHERS _ The 100 mph club: IN short,
pitchers who scare opposing hitters to death. No batter wants to
face members of this club, but they do on an almost daily basis
during the regular season. Baseball's flame throwers are unique ...
and always have been. And the quest to throw a baseball 100 mph
dates through several generations and several unusual inventions to
try to gauge a baseball's speed. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED Friday.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BBO-FAST-SIDE _ (Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
Friday.
</P>
<P>
   MINORBALL _ The Vero Beach Dodgers might play on the same grass
where Jackie Robinson and Sandy Koufax once took the field during
spring training. Alumni of the Class A team include Mike Piazza and
Steve Sax. But that doesn't bring in fans. What keeps them coming
back isn't tradition and ambience. It's fireworks, sky-diving Elvis
impersonators and seat cushion giveaways. A look at the marketing
of minor league baseball. (Ostrowski, Palm Beach Post). WITH
PHOTOS, GRAPHIC.
</P>
