<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, AUGUST 5 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-HAMAS-SUIT-NYT (moved Tuesday, August 1)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, August 1
about a suit against the Syrian government by the family of an
Israeli-American man killed in a 1996 terrorist attack in Jerusalem
misstated the position of Brig. Gen. Ghazi Kanaan, one of two
Syrian defendants. He is the chief of military intelligence, not
commander of the Syrian forces in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
   BC-GOP-PENTAGON-NYT (moved Thursday, August 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, August 3
about the Pentagon's costs for shipping military equipment to a
display near the Republican National Convention in Philadelphia
misstated the amount spent by the Navy. It was $146,796, not
$246,796.
</P>
<P>
   NY-LAZIO (moved Wednesday, August 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, August
2 about Representative Rick A. Lazio's appearance on ``The Bob
Grant Show'' misstated the call letters of the radio station that
carries it. The station is WOR-AM (710), not WWOR.
</P>
<P>
   WRITERS-ON-WRITING (moved Sunday, July 30)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, July 30 by
Hans Koning, about his commitment to serious fiction, misspelled
the title of a novel of his. It is ``Kleber Flight,'' not ``Kleber
Plight.''
</P>
</TEXT>
