<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-05 18:38 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3646 &Cx1f; tab-z
r a BC-PUTIN-GETS-A-GRIP-ECO     08-05 1282
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PUTIN-GETS-A-GRIP-ECONOMIST-775&AMP;add-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE SPOOK VS. THE CROOKS: PUTIN'S PROMISING START  
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
  
 (ATTN: Commentary Editors...NOTE 175-word trim; 1,100 uncut)   (ATTN. EDITORS: The following 925-word (trimmed) material from The
New York Times Syndicate is for use by clients of The Economist.
Nonsubscribers can use this article only by special arrangement.
For purchase information, call 1-888-269-8796, or Debra Weydert at
732-390-4480.)  
 &HT;    
 (NOTE: 175-WORD OPTIONAL TRIM AT 775; TOTAL UNCUT IS 1,100
WORDS.)  
 &HT;    
 (EDITORS: We regret that this material is NOT available to clients
in Canada EXCEPT to The Hamilton (Ontario) Spectator.)  
 &HT;    
 From The Economist magazine  
 c.2000 Economist Newspaper Ltd.  
<TEXT>
 &UR; (Distributed by the New York Times Special Features) &LR;  &QC;
