<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SUNDAY, AUGUST 6 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Sunday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.) 
 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-NERVEGAS-LEAKS-NYT (moved Saturday, July 29)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, July 29
about accusations by workers at the Umatilla Chemical Depot in
Oregon that the Army had concealed leaks of toxic gases gave a
misspelled surname at one point for a lawyer who represents a group
of workers. He is James E. McCandlish, not McClandish.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BUSH-CHENEY-NYT (moved Tuesday, July 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, July 25
about the selection of Dick Cheney as George W. Bush's choice for
vice president misidentified Bruce Buchanan, who teaches courses on
the presidency at the University of Texas and has closely followed
Bush's career. He is a professor of government, not a historian.
</P>
