<HEADLINE>
PERCIVAL, ETHERTON PUT ON DISABLED LIST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND _ Both closer Troy Percival (tendinitis, right elbow)
and starter Seth Etherton (tendinitis, right shoulder) officially
were placed on the disabled list Saturday, joining fellow Anaheim
Angels pitchers Tim Belcher, Jason Dickson, Al Levine, Kent Mercker
and Jarrod Washburn.
</P>
<P>
   Juan Alvarez and Lou Pote were called up from Triple-A Edmonton
to replace Percival and Etherton on the roster.
</P>
<P>
   Matt Wise will take Etherton's spot in the rotation and make his
first major-league start next Wednesday in Anaheim against the Red
Sox. Replacing Percival, who has 25 saves, will be another matter.
</P>
<P>
   Manager Mike Scioscia said the club will use a
closer-by-committee, but Shigetoshi Hasegawa will get most of the
opportunities. Mark Petkovsek might also get some chances.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a definite structure,'' Scioscia said. ``We'll just
run things like if Percy needed a day off.''
</P>
<P>
   Pushing Hasegawa and Petkovsek to the end of games means the
means the middle relief could suffer. And that makes it even more
important for the starters to go deeper into games.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously we haven't gotten production from key components
lately,'' Scioscia said. ``You can call it growing pains, put a lot
of labels on it. But we're in a rut.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Inflammation: Percival's elbow is inflamed because he has
been favoring his surgically repaired shoulder. The Angels hope
that 15 days off will calm the elbow.
</P>
<P>
   ``He needs to take a step back,'' Scioscia said. ``He's not even
a year from surgery. We have to put constraints on how he's used,
how much he's used.''
</P>
<P>
   Percival said his elbow was hurting him last Sunday when he blew
a 6-4 lead in the ninth against the White Sox. But the next day,
Levine was put on the disabled list, so Percival kept his mouth
shut.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wasn't going to say something once Al went down,'' Percival
said. ``It's pretty tough to lose Al and myself at the same time.''
</P>
<P>
   Percival couldn't deny it after his second consecutive blown
save on Friday. He has nine blown saves this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``You look at the blown saves and I don't think he's pitched as
poorly as his record indicates,'' Scioscia said. ``But obviously,
they're on the board.''
</P>
<P>
   __ More breakdowns: Etherton has been hit hard in two of his
past three starts and he says it's the result of a tired shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's nothing I can't throw through,'' he said. ``It's just
fatigue, but I know the best thing for the team is for me to rest.
. . . It's frustrating more than anything. We're trying to win
games in the division race. We need good outings every time out and
I can't help the team.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Sore Mo: First baseman Mo Vaughn was not in the starting
lineup Saturday because of a sore left biceps.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
